Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the
@chicken stock paste{20%g} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g},
bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes}
or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, quarter the @premium tomato mix{125%g}.

Pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} lengthways and discard the core and seeds.

Lay the pepper halves, cut-side up, onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and
season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until slightly softened,
~{5-7%minutes}, then remove and set aside.

While the peppers roast, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
  when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic, @baharat spice mix{1%tbsp}, @tomato puree{30%g}, remaining
chicken stock paste, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce into the beef.
Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once thickened, taste and season again if needed, then divide the beef mixture
between the roasted pepper halves.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} on top and bake on the top shelf of
your oven until the cheese is golden and the peppers are soft, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once cooked, fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{} and stir through the tomatoes and
half the mint. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and pepper if
needed. Stir to combine.

Serve your tabbouleh in #bowls{} topped with a stuffed pepper half.

Sprinkle over the remaining mint and cut any remaining lemon into wedges for squeezing
over.

Enjoy!